column5: Nice, my splake experience was limited to those laker backcross hybrids that we got in Georgian Bay tribs fishing Steelies in the fall in the late 80's. Some were a good size but never as nicely coloured up as that. They were good eating as long as you got them before the September closer as they were not included in the extended fall season.
Yup,splake and white fish at the same spot out from the mouth of the notty in the mid 70,s and up to the late 80,s. Now all gone.  Very nice coloured fish there.
